Copies: 1) Antwerp Mus., N째 807, Photo [...]; 2) Kling Sale, Christie, 28-VI-1935, signed and dated 1630, Panel, 271/2 x 48 in. (Later exh. Slatter 1943, N째 3: 291/2 x 481/2in. Lent by J. Geoffrey Hart); 3) Brussels Exh. 1935, N째 182, Toile, 141 x 281 cm. Princesse Alfons Isenbourg Bernstein; 4) Sale Chillingsworth, Luzern Fischer, 5 Sept.1922, N째 14, Bois, 73 x 124 cm. Panel, 67 x 121 cm; 7) Panco sale, Le Roy, Brussels, 3-4 April 1914, Bois, 73 x 121, signed P. BREVGHEL 1630; 6) ?? [sic] 5? [sic] Cutting from Worcester Mus.
